@startuml sequence_migration
!theme plain

title Migration Workflow: Core to Abstractions (Non-Breaking)

actor Developer as dev
participant "CodeGenerator.Abstractions\n(new project)" as abs
participant "CodeGenerator.Core\n(existing)" as core
participant "Framework Modules\n(Flask, Python, etc.)" as fw
participant "CodeGenerator.DotNet" as dotnet
participant "NuGet" as nuget

== Phase 1: Create Abstractions Project ==
dev -> abs : Create CodeGenerator.Abstractions.csproj\nwith minimal deps
dev -> abs : Move interfaces, base models,\nenums from Core
dev -> core : Add ProjectReference to Abstractions
dev -> core : Add [TypeForwardedTo] attributes\nfor all moved types

note right of core
  TypeForwardedTo ensures that any
  assembly compiled against the OLD
  Core namespace still resolves types
  at runtime from Abstractions.
end note

== Phase 2: Update Namespace Strategy ==
dev -> abs : Keep original namespaces\n(CodeGenerator.Core.Syntax, etc.)
note right of abs
  Option A: Keep old namespaces (zero breaking changes)
  Option B: New namespaces + type forwarding
  Recommendation: Option A for v1
end note

== Phase 3: Update Framework Modules ==
dev -> fw : Replace Core ProjectReference\nwith Abstractions ProjectReference
dev -> fw : Verify build (no code changes needed\nif namespaces preserved)

== Phase 4: Move Heavy Deps to DotNet ==
dev -> core : Remove Roslyn, LibGit2Sharp,\nMediatR, AutoMapper, Octokit,\nEnvDTE, TextCopy packages
dev -> dotnet : Verify DotNet has its own\nheavy dependencies
dev -> core : Keep DotLiquid, Humanizer,\nSerilog, Newtonsoft.Json

== Phase 5: Publish ==
dev -> nuget : Publish CodeGenerator.Abstractions\n(v1.0.0)
dev -> nuget : Publish CodeGenerator.Core\n(v1.3.0 - with Abstractions dep)
dev -> nuget : Publish updated framework modules

== Phase 6: Verify ==
dev -> fw : Run integration tests\nacross all 8 framework modules
dev -> dotnet : Run DotNet generation tests
dev -> core : Run Core unit tests

@enduml
